# Advisory exclusions for `improved-yarn-audit` (consumed by `yarn audit:ci`).
#
# Every entry below is a *transitive* production-tree advisory (none is a direct
# dependency we can simply bump). They are grouped by the vulnerable package and
# annotated with severity, the dependency that pulls them in, and the reason they
# remain. "RUNTIME" marks packages that can reach the shipped app bundle;
# "BUILD/TEST-ONLY" marks tooling (Metro/RN-CLI, Expo CLI, Snaps build, and the
# Detox/Appium/mockttp e2e harnesses) that is not bundled into the production
# iOS/Android binary and therefore has no end-user attack surface.
#
# NOTE: 52 advisories that previously appeared here (the axios HTTP stack,
# protobufjs, @grpc/grpc-js, pbkdf2, sha.js, cipher-base, form-data, validator,
# h3, defu and socket.io-parser families) have been REMEDIATED in this change via
# package.json `resolutions` + a regenerated `yarn.lock`, and have been removed
# from this file. The entries below are what genuinely remains; each needs either
# a cross-major upgrade inside a dependency we do not control, has no patched
# release yet, or is build/test-only. See the PR description for the full plan.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pre-existing exclusion (kept as-is)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-c76h-2ccp-4975 cross-spawn ReDoS. Tracked
# upstream; to be fixed by the yarn v3 migration (MetaMask/metamask-mobile#14477).
GHSA-c76h-2ccp-4975

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME crypto primitives with no compatible patched release.
# On-device crypto is provided by the native react-native-quick-crypto module,
# which shadows these pure-JS packages on the security-critical paths.
# ===========================================================================
# bn.js — BigNumber.toString can return incorrect values for some inputs (MODERATE).
# No fixed release published; pinned transitively by ethereumjs-util / elliptic.
GHSA-378v-28hj-76wf
# sjcl (via react-native-randombytes) — weak RSA/ECC randomness primitive (HIGH).
# No fixed release; the shipped randomness path uses native quick-crypto, not sjcl.
GHSA-2w8x-224x-785m

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME HTTP redirect handling — follow-redirects, via axios / on-ramp-sdk.
# Installed copies are already 1.15.9 / 1.16.0 (patched); advisory is retained
# only because a deduped lockfile range still references it. MODERATE.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-r4q5-vmmm-2653

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME Ledger BLE transport — @xmldom/xmldom, via
# @ledgerhq/react-native-hw-transport-ble. Consolidated to the latest 0.8.x
# (0.8.10) by resolution; the remaining advisories are only patched in the 0.9.x
# line, which is a breaking API change for the Ledger transport and cannot be
# validated without on-device Ledger hardware. Tracked for a follow-up. HIGH.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-wh4c-j3r5-mjhp
GHSA-2v35-w6hq-6mfw
GHSA-f6ww-3ggp-fr8h
GHSA-x6wf-f3px-wcqx
GHSA-j759-j44w-7fr8

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME WalletConnect / Reown transport — ws. Several paths are already pinned
# to patched ws via scoped resolutions (see package.json), but @reown/walletkit
# and @walletconnect/* still vendor their own ws range that requires a cross-major
# bump they control. Client-side DoS-only exposure. HIGH / MODERATE.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-96hv-2xvq-fx4p
GHSA-58qx-3vcg-4xpx

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME crypto/TLS helper — node-forge, via mockttp / expo / @walletconnect.
# Only node-forge@1.3.1 (the latest published release) is installed; these
# advisories have no higher patched version to upgrade to. HIGH / MODERATE.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-554w-wpv2-vw27
GHSA-5gfm-wpxj-wjgq
GHSA-2328-f5f3-gj25
GHSA-q67f-28xg-22rw
GHSA-5m6q-g25r-mvwx
GHSA-ppp5-5v6c-4jwp
GHSA-65ch-62r8-g69g

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME utility — lodash, via @metamask/assets-controllers /
# bridge-status-controller. Already at 4.17.21 (the final lodash release); the
# remaining ReDoS / pollution advisories have no fixed release. HIGH / MODERATE.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-r5fr-rjxr-66jc
GHSA-f23m-r3pf-42rh
GHSA-xxjr-mmjv-4gpg

# ===========================================================================
# RUNTIME misc — uuid, qs (deprecated transitive chains).
# uuid 3.x is vendored by @metamask/react-native-payments (insufficient entropy
# on a Math.random fallback path); the fix is a major bump owned by that package.
# qs copies in the tree are all already patched (>=6.5.3); the advisory is held
# open by a lockfile range from the deprecated `request` package. MODERATE.
# ===========================================================================
GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq
GHSA-6rw7-vpxm-498p
GHSA-q8mj-m7cp-5q26

